  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Climate Change Adaptation and Local Capacity Building in Somoto</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project seeks to help 3 communities in the municipality of Somoto, department of Madriz, to build resilience to the effects of climate change, through three objectives:
1. Improve access and availability of clean water for 100 households through the construction of 12 wells, local capacity building and hygiene education.
2. Improve access to food  for 95 families, by improving and diversifying crop production and household consumption.
3. Strengthen the capacity and skills of 100 families in local risk management, so they have  tools to prevent disasters caused by natural and human phenomena.</narrative>
  </description>
